<TITLE> U-17 side thrash Nepalese counterparts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Under-17 team recorded an emphatic eight-wicket win over their Nepalese counterparts in first of three friendship matches at the T.U ground in Nepal on Sunday. The visitors raced to 65 for two in 27.2 overs in reply to the hosts' 62 all out in 30.2 overs. Put in to bat first, the Nepal U-17 side were bundled out for a paltry total as Mohammad Sentu wrecked the top order taking three for 12 while Asif Hasan and Mehdi Hasan grabbed two wickets each to clear the tail. In reply, Bangladesh lost Jayanta Das (4) and Shahnaz Ahmed (14), but opener Ashiqul Alam (17) and Mehdi Hasan (12) remained unbeaten to steer the visitors home. bd
